    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Construction using materials with less thermal mass, and with a high strength to weight ratio. Examples of lightweight construction elements include plywood, plasterboard, steel studs, or frames without walls.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052038/Hyde, Climate Responsive Design (2000)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>建造中使用較少的保溫材料，以及強度-重量比極高的材料。輕質構造元件的幾種例子包括膠合板、石膏板以及輕鋼龍骨。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
